<p local-id=3D"ca32f02b4a14">Text</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"3882a28b-c787-4b63-80cb-3497eb9c2f52" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"42ccb3834c7f">The name of the guest.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"94855446-04c5-475a-a6dd-cb4b6ecda3dc">
<td data-local-id=3D"eead42b4-6f29-4716-bab5-931f9e7297c2" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"5b59f08dd5ae"><strong>Current Room Category</strong></p></td=
>
<td data-local-id=3D"16cb68fe-2c2c-4dbc-99b1-82a5dea6634b" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"226ea74e8eb9">Text (GUID)</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"6cf6fc97-2eec-4e7a-96e7-d67e4971ed21" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"0cef4362a8c8">The identifier of the room category the guest =
is currently assigned to.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"2a3e969f-38f5-4b46-ad9c-9a4f2f4a70bf">
<td data-local-id=3D"266b985e-1e36-4297-8e98-c6497af9f6d0" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"6616a392045e"><strong>Target Room Category</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"6b3c047a-7649-4f84-bf4d-ad5796601a6b" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"ce9cdba54914">Text (GUID)</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"1872d5be-f4b2-4104-9e5d-2785725703aa" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"65e23002e2cc">The identifier of the room category the system=
 attempted to upgrade to (empty if no matching upgrade path was found).</p>=
</td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"731a74b7-ff70-4a7b-b58d-b9d26620d04e">
<td data-local-id=3D"ad93f3ec-6de4-4d5a-aadd-38bc95fe909f" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"7c45eb99812c"><strong>Failure Reason</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"7a20aa19-5d5b-41f5-ae6e-1357ba8656d2" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"27ab350c2d94">Text</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"f6f6f977-bd4f-4782-978c-9dce1b39bbe3" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"6ed05943405e">Why the upgrade failed. Possible values:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"00606e1c-ca11-4e9d-a6d3-e3e686ca6b4e">
<li local-id=3D"5d0e9323-c8bd-4f93-b45b-a4809caf9422">
<p local-id=3D"50e7eacd69a4"><code>NO_AVAILABILITY</code> =E2=80=94 The tar=
get room category has no available rooms (after accounting for the availabi=
lity buffer).</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"5f783c12-b4a1-4452-87a4-4d6937a804b4">
<p local-id=3D"c4b4a7d38efc"><code>CAP_REACHED</code> =E2=80=94 The maximum=
 number of upgrades for this run has been reached.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"98543d32-4e55-43fb-bf6b-a88137c593d6">
<p local-id=3D"3a45884e60e0"><code>NO_CATEGORY_FOUND</code> =E2=80=94 The r=
eservation's current room category does not match any defined upgrade path.=
</p></li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"66281ac0-9003-47de-925f-80af8cb5f3c2">
<td data-local-id=3D"f741c7d3-a4ea-4967-a9ad-417bc4911b0e" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"edb2445602fc"><strong>Check-in Date</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"08111670-b106-4bd9-96c2-91aac274c702" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"12c0d381b9bf">Text (Date)</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"d4fd1b5c-19b1-4dde-a4f4-265728197b81" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"13eb021226ff">The check-in date of the reservation (format: =
<code>DD-MM-YYYY</code>).</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"6a3c7c3b-2564-41a9-86dc-5e5f4aec4c20">
<td data-local-id=3D"f8cbd751-f5bb-4ae7-aee6-5f50cc2e45fc" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"732c28f60a99"><strong>Check-out Date</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"86ebf66a-dd58-4313-b507-a40fda307993" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"424122d210bb">Text (Date)</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"20aab043-e721-498e-9eb2-b82eb523dee5" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"dd1882f58a6b">The check-out date of the reservation (format:=
 <code>DD-MM-YYYY</code>).</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr local-id=3D"870ae107-229e-4184-b9d0-8c2c17c1de14">
<h2 local-id=3D"4083256f91fa" id=3D"UpgradeAssignedRoomCategory-CooldownSet=
tings">Cooldown Settings</h2>
<p local-id=3D"c38e22eddc32">The cooldown feature prevents the action from =
processing the same reservation again within a defined time window. This is=
 useful when a workflow may be triggered multiple times in quick succession=
 and you want to avoid attempting duplicate upgrades for the same reservati=
on.</p>
<p local-id=3D"f54cdacdd1e3">Cooldown settings are located in the <strong>C=
ooldown</strong> section of the component settings, which is collapsed by d=
efault.</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"c6=
e9c44f-b5e5-47a1-a575-fd9cecbee256" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"3d9a23b4-8d08-478e-a18d-fec885fc5e65">
<th data-local-id=3D"5584a105-f664-47ac-9618-6c7f41ecdfad" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"38c370419992">Setting</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"6d1ee0fd-b341-498d-b2d5-e47c6bbb795f" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"76e67ce23b4b">Required</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"238a143e-5bfd-4cda-b826-74b2e9057541" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"02c1a03cce32">Description</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"ffe479f1-ab50-4c13-b8ee-5cddc0b4ba26">
<td data-local-id=3D"a4dfe724-9a61-4519-8e29-009f7379fc0c" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"9fa74338fdb9"><strong>Cooldown period</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"ca64bf4d-877d-43da-a594-08ad3115846a" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"2c5e54c08c61"><strong>Optional</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"b7cf5409-672b-440f-abdf-41ed7f6c28ea" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"7e0a32f6381d">The number of time units during which the acti=
on will not run again for the same tracked entity. Set to <code>0</code> (d=
efault) to disable the cooldown.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"b005e344-3c6d-404a-8b03-84366b87b3bf">
<td data-local-id=3D"7d70c6a3-b40e-4b26-8acb-316041106d3d" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"4d3d8931c0dc"><strong>Unit</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"aa254b52-2271-4c99-9ac1-a99b2f6ae1fb" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"437e5ff20e1d"><strong>Optional</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"b1c81208-bd40-492b-a704-50bc6b138a98" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"dbf20e74d73d">The time unit for the cooldown period. Options=
: <strong>Minutes</strong>, <strong>Hours</strong>, <strong>Days</strong> (=
default), <strong>Weeks</strong>.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"8df45a6e-87e1-4be7-8541-42f6bfaa9b2e">
<td data-local-id=3D"7fa145e1-8cdb-4713-abe6-319af3eb2d1b" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"455f1df37210"><strong>Track by</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"4d8310e4-21be-424f-b669-15df06d3ce5d" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"39c7084a6816"><strong>Optional</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"8e7c7a03-1c9f-47a9-8d02-ca57c5562c1f" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"324a51c1128e">Determines the scope of the cooldown. Only vis=
ible when the cooldown period is greater than 0.</p>
<ul local-id=3D"b29e5b4c-e23d-41d3-8484-f68f84e35941">
<li local-id=3D"4aa08a42-8281-4730-8ac0-2ee000ae3b6c">
<p local-id=3D"ee3f6f4aa8b6"><strong>None</strong> (default) =E2=80=94 A si=
ngle global cooldown window for this component instance.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"daffbcc6-d51b-4318-9d01-530c2370e668">
<p local-id=3D"e9b5c158872c"><strong>Reservation</strong> =E2=80=94 Each re=
servation gets its own independent cooldown window. Reservations that are s=
till within their cooldown period are filtered out before processing.</p></=
li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h3 local-id=3D"3f294e92e5e2" id=3D"UpgradeAssignedRoomCategory-CooldownOut=
put">Cooldown Output</h3>
<p local-id=3D"c9cdbe1d3d42">When the cooldown is active (i.e., the action =
is skipped because it already ran within the cooldown window), the componen=
t outputs the following on the <strong>cooldown</strong> port:</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"7c=
431152-bf2a-420d-b827-6e3330bb5242" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"f0fc65ea-6174-441d-8f5b-61de558e1c1d">
<th data-local-id=3D"5bc45e83-347d-4583-b6db-3e82322f22b8" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"82425e16ca5a">Field</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"0a24bb13-6554-460b-a118-5d4e00b2251c" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"ef6029da5284">Type</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"72f6579c-b983-428f-b09b-be404bcec7f8" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"00be5b5370f6">Description</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"78215378-dfcc-4b2d-a859-de93a31977bf">
<td data-local-id=3D"9bb70281-e66c-4c11-9a90-a0e801a24b9c" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"f377352e511e"><strong>Expires at</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"1373cb2e-d771-461c-b754-b5601324b38c" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"67cc7fe5c8a0">Date &amp; Time</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"7077baa3-d16a-4097-9821-36aa9dc00cb9" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c5320845a2de">The date and time (UTC) when the cooldown wind=
ow expires and the action can run again.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"05244467-37fd-4796-9db2-3e1c71baa432">
<td data-local-id=3D"43ae097a-0e84-4515-8a56-260a0fe724aa" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"eedfc2daa8e1"><strong>Remaining (minutes)</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"0a506bac-5e12-4b6f-b759-ae1488248a32" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"35efcdbfe9db">Number</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"3be0f941-1183-4a37-ade4-239b2ceca262" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"5abb35bd74c3">The number of minutes remaining until the cool=
down expires.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"daea3f036b53"><strong>Tip:</strong> You can connect the <str=
ong>cooldown</strong> port to other components to handle the cooldown scena=
rio =E2=80=94 for example, to log that the upgrade was skipped or to notify=
 an operator.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"3f252f29-72f4-490f-a6ed-1aaf2646929e">
<h2 local-id=3D"18dbd64c9cdf" id=3D"UpgradeAssignedRoomCategory-HowItWorks"=
>How It Works</h2>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"e8cae9e9-ca13-44de-9d6b-1c53673ef6d6">
<li local-id=3D"7f0e2f80-54f6-4b44-93f7-a6ac94988c02">
<p local-id=3D"760c75818425">The component receives a list of reservation I=
Ds and upgrade path definitions from the previous step in the workflow (or =
from manually configured values).</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c45e1ce9-9882-41fc-89f4-53c0ee81f873">
<p local-id=3D"420beba1be2f">If a cooldown is configured and active, reserv=
ations still within their cooldown window are filtered out before processin=
g. If all reservations are filtered, the cooldown information is sent to th=
e <strong>cooldown</strong> port.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"769eb4b2-a3d4-40a4-9c34-86b2ac0604ae">
<p local-id=3D"4f3fcd05cb7b">For each reservation, the system looks up the =
guest's currently assigned room category.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d7c02bbf-8ed7-428d-b20e-379c6bd8af6b">
<p local-id=3D"6e886a3b35dd">The system checks whether the reservation's cu=
rrent room category matches any defined upgrade path. Upgrade paths support=
 <strong>cascading</strong>: if a direct upgrade target has no availability=
, the system follows the chain to try the next target in the path (e.g., St=
andard =E2=86=92 Deluxe =E2=86=92 Suite).</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"48ec2d8e-86d9-4181-96e3-5b9a16cdb5ef">
<p local-id=3D"67f3acd0ee5e">Before performing an upgrade, the system check=
s <strong>real-time room availability</strong> in the target category. This=
 accounts for existing reservations, room blocks, and the resource hierarch=
y (parent/child rooms). The upgrade is only attempted if the number of avai=
lable rooms exceeds the configured availability buffer (or the per-category=
 override, if set).</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"160bf5f3-163f-432f-a08d-5b78ab5f7577">
<p local-id=3D"da630178422c">If the <strong>Max Rooms to Upgrade</strong> c=
ap has been reached, all remaining reservations are marked as failed with t=
he <code>CAP_REACHED</code> reason.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"91e244da-f605-4eb4-8099-b542fbd7bebe">
<p local-id=3D"b9ce3adaedee">Reservations whose assigned room is locked (ma=
nually assigned by staff) are skipped and reported as failed.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ee7785fe-6092-4d01-a2a7-a00d1aa2b772">
<p local-id=3D"7567bc9c9dd2">Successfully upgraded reservations are sent to=
 the <strong>upgraded</strong> output port. Failed reservations are sent to=
 the <strong>failed</strong> output port with a reason.</p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"7b18deb78b46"><strong>Important:</strong> Reservations are p=
rocessed sequentially in the order they are provided. Each successful upgra=
de updates the availability count for subsequent reservations, ensuring acc=
urate capacity tracking within a single run.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"281d35c2-b752-4461-88d4-85b8749ffdd9">
<h2 local-id=3D"01ec2859322b" id=3D"UpgradeAssignedRoomCategory-UpgradePath=
Cascading">Upgrade Path Cascading</h2>
<p local-id=3D"2938be62cefd">Upgrade paths can be chained to create cascadi=
ng upgrade sequences. The system uses the defined paths to build a graph, a=
nd attempts upgrades in order of proximity (closest upgrade first).</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"dcec1fc2e0ae" id=3D"UpgradeAssignedRoomCategory-Cascadingac=
rosssteps">Cascading across steps</h3>
<p local-id=3D"a49918bbbba5">You can chain upgrade paths so that when a dir=
ect upgrade target has no availability, the system follows the chain to try=
 the next step.</p>
<p local-id=3D"0110c9b70eaf"><strong>Example:</strong> If you define the fo=
llowing upgrade paths:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"7712625d-85e3-40d3-9bca-5dbbff68b1ec">
<li local-id=3D"8885abf1-cda5-4fd9-9d03-44bbaaa80fa3">
<p local-id=3D"5143a8e56f2a">Standard =E2=86=92 Deluxe</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4ba6342d-2f64-4625-8fec-15d620b9252b">
<p local-id=3D"92de0deea95a">Deluxe =E2=86=92 Suite</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"9bb1d4e2cb9f">A guest currently in a <strong>Standard</stron=
g> room will first be considered for a <strong>Deluxe</strong> upgrade. If =
no Deluxe rooms are available (after accounting for the buffer), the system=
 will follow the chain and attempt to upgrade directly to a <strong>Suite</=
strong>.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"eeaf18f05793" id=3D"UpgradeAssignedRoomCategory-Multipletar=
getsperstep">Multiple targets per step</h3>
<p local-id=3D"3d33dd903443">You can also define multiple upgrade targets f=
or the same source category within a single step. The system will try each =
target in order until one succeeds.</p>
<p local-id=3D"07467b365fdf"><strong>Example:</strong> If you define the fo=
llowing upgrade paths:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"b2775c5c-5448-47bf-b3c3-57566758f89b">
<li local-id=3D"53ba8acb-2f59-4964-add2-4b18e35566cc">
<p local-id=3D"cced3c210302">Standard =E2=86=92 Deluxe</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"bdd9f6d8-89a1-453d-9bbf-79fbe1e1c917">
<p local-id=3D"aaa44ce360c7">Standard =E2=86=92 Superior Deluxe</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"b376362dc00e">A guest currently in a <strong>Standard</stron=
g> room will first be considered for a <strong>Deluxe</strong> upgrade. If =
no Deluxe rooms are available, the system will then try <strong>Superior De=
luxe</strong> before moving on.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"e0b6309c69af" id=3D"UpgradeAssignedRoomCategory-Combiningbo=
thstrategies">Combining both strategies</h3>
<p local-id=3D"14acc6f4bfe2">These two approaches can be combined for maxim=
um flexibility. You can define multiple targets at the same level <em>and</=
em> chain them to further steps.</p>
<p local-id=3D"2e08f3a8a0e9"><strong>Example:</strong> If you define the fo=
llowing upgrade paths:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"7bd4c74c-7ed1-441c-a41e-b7755a8b20f5">
<li local-id=3D"8458ee4c-92d6-4d23-9f19-45c8c028f971">
<p local-id=3D"3c40681819de">Standard =E2=86=92 Deluxe</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"bf326110-a713-4ebb-8fde-339926b123a3">
<p local-id=3D"faa75e661730">Standard =E2=86=92 Superior Deluxe</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"eb4b70f3-45e3-4495-870f-55e5502d1d3d">
<p local-id=3D"e25c12052503">Deluxe =E2=86=92 Suite</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4e9eeda1-3511-43fd-959c-8d7b673fa272">
<p local-id=3D"d7b9adfb41e2">Superior Deluxe =E2=86=92 Suite</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"4f225e7eb879">A guest in a <strong>Standard</strong> room wi=
ll be evaluated in this order: <strong>Deluxe</strong> first, then <strong>=
Superior Deluxe</strong>, and finally <strong>Suite</strong> (reached throu=
gh the cascading chain). The first target with available rooms (above the b=
uffer threshold) wins.</p>
<p local-id=3D"fe8f818ac21c"><strong>Note:</strong> Reservations that are a=
lready assigned to a category that is a target of an upgrade path (but not =
a source) are automatically skipped =E2=80=94 they are considered already a=
t the end of an upgrade path and do not appear in the failed output.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"30ef5f8a-9e93-4a65-b098-8d9e924e0ac6">
<h2 local-id=3D"6bd355a9c16c" id=3D"UpgradeAssignedRoomCategory-FailureReas=
ons">Failure Reasons</h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"51=
7a2272-3546-4221-8979-9dc6f12bbf90" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"a5284933-e6ca-495e-aefb-7fe172ce8f1f">
<th data-local-id=3D"ba59c6d9-a11a-4046-8238-67386e8aa188" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"93b6c581b1b3">Reason</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"a8acfc63-b64b-409c-a75f-8775684574de" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"f237a4de7590">Description</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"59fc44ca-a1d2-4a8e-bbc4-ca1064d27934">
<td data-local-id=3D"b2c6a78e-c139-4e51-9627-d81662dd57ae" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"72ccb4feb3f1"><code>NO_AVAILABILITY</code></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"588372bd-0e54-4368-bf23-5f5babbb762b" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"eb6fe5061370">All target room categories in the upgrade path=
 are fully occupied or do not have enough rooms available above the configu=
red availability buffer. This also applies when the reservation's assigned =
room is locked by staff.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"28a56532-60aa-4546-982c-f20303305fb7">
<td data-local-id=3D"ea6fd43c-2aa2-49bd-ab93-d7e3bd8160d1" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"8d0e6c45818b"><code>CAP_REACHED</code></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"78140cb8-c82c-4939-b5e0-1769355ca47d" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"9e8058e75c0c">The maximum number of upgrades (<strong>Max Ro=
oms to Upgrade</strong>) for this run has already been reached. The reserva=
tion was not evaluated for availability.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"3c7cfade-f857-48ad-a167-9a35cfe9f75b">
<td data-local-id=3D"c36eb285-08e0-4ef3-899c-0a86e4ae5f43" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"964bfac66065"><code>NO_CATEGORY_FOUND</code></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"4020eb52-b510-420e-8fd7-4eda4cc5a438" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"f1a6b2275e18">The reservation's current room category does n=
ot match any <em>From</em> category in the defined upgrade paths, and it is=
 not a target category either.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr local-id=3D"1e680afe-ba87-41fa-9635-5f0e8702157c">
<h2 local-id=3D"632a2ab3b05b" id=3D"UpgradeAssignedRoomCategory-ExampleUseC=
ases">Example Use Cases</h2>
<ul local-id=3D"7f45743a-e285-4ef5-b834-26b09694517e">
<li local-id=3D"4a2b2474-d77f-481b-b213-608a0a19cb2b">
<p local-id=3D"3b0eee309ce3"><strong>Daily automated upgrades</strong> =E2=
=80=94 Schedule a workflow to run each morning that fetches today's arrivin=
g reservations and upgrades eligible guests from Standard to Deluxe rooms, =
keeping 2 Deluxe rooms in reserve for walk-in guests.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"bf14246d-ad5b-40c6-83ba-477470b2ad14">
<p local-id=3D"8113a99d8f94"><strong>VIP guest upgrades</strong> =E2=80=94 =
When a reservation is tagged as VIP, automatically attempt to upgrade the g=
uest to the best available room category using cascading paths (Standard =
=E2=86=92 Deluxe =E2=86=92 Suite), with a per-category buffer to always kee=
p 1 Suite available.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"6db8ebc2-15d5-444b-b602-c48e5808e3ae">
<p local-id=3D"ba0668bbb5e8"><strong>Occupancy optimization</strong> =E2=80=
=94 Run upgrades for all arriving reservations when occupancy in higher cat=
egories is below a threshold, maximizing room utilization while maintaining=
 availability buffers.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"55446c07-97c1-4bbc-b425-ea0e89460317">
<p local-id=3D"85487fa925b5"><strong>Controlled batch upgrades</strong> =E2=
=80=94 Use the <strong>Max Rooms to Upgrade</strong> setting to limit upgra=
des to 5 per run, ensuring a gradual rollout that can be reviewed by staff.=
</p></li>
</ul>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
